President Trump held a meeting at Trump National Golf Club in Bedminster, New Jersey to discuss prison reform. The President expressed his support for prison reform and highlighted the importance of helping former inmates find jobs and reintegrate into society. Several governors, including Matt Bevin of Kentucky, Phil Bryant of Mississippi, and John Bel Edwards of Louisiana, shared their experiences with prison reform and the positive impact it has had in their states. Attorney General Pam Bondi of Florida also spoke about the importance of providing job opportunities for former inmates. Secretary of Labor Alex Acosta and Secretary of Energy Rick Perry also attended the meeting and discussed the positive effects of prison reform on the economy. Overall, the meeting focused on the need to improve reentry programs, provide vocational training, and strengthen community bonds with law enforcement to ensure the successful reintegration of former inmates into society.